A monk is meant to have endurance and stamina and the way most choose to
start building it up is by running. This choice has become the standard by
which a monks basic stamina is measured. A master asks you to run fifty laps
at a good pace. With all your travels around the lands this seems a rather
simple final task to achieve so you readily agree to it.',0,0,0);
The path leads further under the overhang and as you progress you feel
unfriendly eyes watching you. There are more crates here, lining the
path, but those still with occupants look at you with pleading, begging
eyes. There is something else moving through the area of the crates,
but you cannot see what it is. All you know is it is stalking you and
it is a feeling you do not like at all.',0,0,0);
